Global Air Insulated Switchgear Market Insights
Air Insulated Switchgear Market size was valued at USD 23.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 32.1 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 4.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Air Insulated Switchgear Market Overview
The global Air Insulated Switchgear (AIS) market is valued at approximately USD 17.9 billion in 2024 and is anticipated to grow at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.1% from 2025 to 2032. AIS is widely used in electrical power distribution systems for switching and protection of electrical equipment. The growth of the market is driven by increasing demand for reliable power distribution infrastructure and the rapid urbanization across emerging economies. Governments’ focus on renewable energy sources and smart grid technologies also contribute significantly to market expansion. The Asia-Pacific region is expected to maintain its dominant market share during the forecast period, with rising investments in power generation and infrastructure development in countries like China and India.

